name: Sanchez-Baracaldo_2017
dataset.notes: This is the alignment of chloroplast and cyanobacteria. The concanated alignment has 9 more sites than the alignment that the authors provided.
study.reference: SÃ¡nchez-Baracaldo P, Raven J A, Pisani D, et al. Early photosynthetic eukaryotes inhabited low-salinity habitats[J]. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 2017, 114(37): E7737-E7745.

name: Ran_2018_dna
dataset.notes: This is the codon dataset described in the paper, that contains all three codon positions, in frame for each locus
study.reference: Ran J-H, Shen T-T, Wang M-M, Wang X-Q (2018) Phylogenomics resolves the deep phylogeny of seed plants and indicates partial convergent or homoplastic evolution between Gnetales and angiosperms. Proceedings of the Royal Society B 285(1881): 20181012.

name: Ran_2018_aa
dataset.notes: This is the amino acid dataset described in the paper. It was generated by translating the codon dataset in this repository Ran_2018_dna
study.reference: Ran J-H, Shen T-T, Wang M-M, Wang X-Q (2018) Phylogenomics resolves the deep phylogeny of seed plants and indicates partial convergent or homoplastic evolution between Gnetales and angiosperms. Proceedings of the Royal Society B 285(1881): 20181012.

name: Wu_2018_dna
dataset.notes: This is the cds_5162.zip dataset, loci were in frame and codon positions were annotated as such.
study.reference: Wu, S., Edwards, S., & Liu, L. (2018). Genome-scale DNA sequence data and the evolutionary history of placental mammals. Data in brief, 18, 1972-1975.

name: Ruhfel_2014_dna
dataset.notes: This is a study of plastid genomes
study.reference: Ruhfel, B. R., Gitzendanner, M. A., Soltis, P. S., Soltis, D. E., & Burleigh, J. G. (2014). From algae to angiospermsâ€“inferring the phylogeny of green plants (Viridiplantae) from 360 plastid genomes. BMC evolutionary biology, 14(1), 1-27.

name: Ruhfel_2014_aa
dataset.notes: This is a study of plastid genomes. The amino acid dataset was produced by translating each locus.
study.reference: Ruhfel, B. R., Gitzendanner, M. A., Soltis, P. S., Soltis, D. E., & Burleigh, J. G. (2014). From algae to angiospermsâ€“inferring the phylogeny of green plants (Viridiplantae) from 360 plastid genomes. BMC evolutionary biology, 14(1), 1-27.

name: Wu_2018_aa
dataset.notes: This is the cds_5162.zip dataset. The amino acid dataset was produced by translating each locus.
study.reference: Wu, S., Edwards, S., & Liu, L. (2018). Genome-scale DNA sequence data and the evolutionary history of placental mammals. Data in brief, 18, 1972-1975.

name: Branstetter_2017
dataset.notes: This is the dataset Hym-187T-F75, which is the dataset used for the main figure in the paper. One of many datasets available from the link under "Alignment supermatrices" on Dryad.
study.reference: Branstetter MG, Danforth BN, Pitts JP, Faircloth BC, Ward PS, Buffington ML, Gates MW, Kula RR, Brady SG (2017) Phylogenomic Insights into the Evolution of Stinging Wasps and the Origins of Ants and Bees. Current Biology 27(7): 1019-1025.

name: Reddy_2017
dataset.notes: this is the dataset Reddy_sup_fileS5_EB2taxset.nex, which was used to produce figure 3 in the paper from this link https://datadryad.org/bitstream/handle/10255/dryad.141055/Reddy_sup_fileS5_alignments.tar.gz?sequence=1. The charsets in this repository are the main charsets derived from that file (88 in total).
study.reference: Reddy S, Kimball RT, Pandey A, Hosner PA, Braun MJ, Hackett SJ, Han K, Harshman J, Huddleston CJ, Kingston S, Marks BD, Miglia KJ, Moore WS, Sheldon FH, Witt CC, Yuri T, Braun EL (2017) Why do phylogenomic data sets yield conflicting trees? Data type influences the avian tree of life more than taxon sampling. Systematic Biology 66(5): 857-879.

name: Liu_2019_dna
dataset.notes: This dataset includes nuclear, chloroplast and mitochondrial alignments.Some taxa only used one of nuclear or organellar alignments.
study.reference: Liu Y, Johnson M G, Cox C J, et al. Resolution of the ordinal phylogeny of mosses using targeted exons from organellar and nuclear genomes[J]. Nature Communications, 2019, 10(1): 1485.

dataset.notes: This dataset includes nuclear, chloroplast and mitochondrial alignments.Some taxa only used one of nuclear or organellar alignments.
study.reference: Liu Y, Johnson M G, Cox C J, et al. Resolution of the ordinal phylogeny of mosses using targeted exons from organellar and nuclear genomes[J]. Nature Communications, 2019, 10(1): 1485.
